  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_9' aria-label=\" Vijay Kumar Joshi versus Akash Tripathi & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('9','2025','2025_6_402_413','2025INSC670'); ><font size='4'> <strong>VIJAY KUMAR JOSHI<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>AKASH TRIPATHI & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 6 S.C.R. 402</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 670</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010002032025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, PRASANNA BHALACHANDRA VARALE</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose with regards to admissibility of pension to the employees of the Co-operative Societies who were absorbed with the Madhya Pradesh State Electricity Board (MPSEB); if the answer to the same is yes then what would be the length of service to be counted i.e. would also be counted for determining the qualifying period for calculation of pension or only the service rendered after absorption in the MPSEB would be counted. Headnotes&dagger; Madhya Pradesh Civil Services (Pension) Rules &ndash; rr.3(p), 12(2), 13(1) &ndash; Admissibility of pension to<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 12-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 6652/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('9','2025','2025_6_402_413','2025INSC670','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto